  33:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****   [..]
  34:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     *** Initialization ***
  35:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     ======================
  36:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     [..]
  37:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      As prerequisite, fill in the HAL_OSPI_MspInit() :
  38:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Enable OctoSPI and OctoSPIM clocks interface with __HAL_RCC_OSPIx_CLK_ENABLE().
  39:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Reset OctoSPI Peripheral with __HAL_RCC_OSPIx_FORCE_RESET() and __HAL_RCC_OSPIx_RELEASE_RE
  40:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Enable the clocks for the OctoSPI GPIOS with __HAL_RCC_GPIOx_CLK_ENABLE().
  41:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Configure these OctoSPI pins in alternate mode using HAL_GPIO_Init().
  42:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) If interrupt or DMA mode is used, enable and configure OctoSPI global
  43:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****          interrupt with HAL_NVIC_SetPriority() and HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ().
  44:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) If DMA mode is used, enable the clocks for the OctoSPI DMA channel
  45:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****          with __HAL_RCC_DMAx_CLK_ENABLE(), configure DMA with HAL_DMA_Init(),
  46:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****          link it with OctoSPI handle using __HAL_LINKDMA(), enable and configure
  47:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****          DMA channel global interrupt with HAL_NVIC_SetPriority() and HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ().
  48:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     [..]
  49:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      Configure the fifo threshold, the dual-quad mode, the memory type, the
  50:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      device size, the CS high time, the free running clock, the clock mode,
  51:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      the wrap size, the clock prescaler, the sample shifting, the hold delay
  52:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      and the CS boundary using the HAL_OSPI_Init() function.
  53:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     [..]
  54:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      When using Hyperbus, configure the RW recovery time, the access time,
  55:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      the write latency and the latency mode using the HAL_OSPI_HyperbusCfg()
  56:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      function.
  57:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c **** 
  58:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     *** Indirect functional mode ***
  59:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     ================================
  60:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     [..]
  61:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      In regular mode, configure the command sequence using the HAL_OSPI_Command()
  62:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      or HAL_OSPI_Command_IT() functions :
  63:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Instruction phase : the mode used and if present the size, the instruction
  64:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****          opcode and the DTR mode.
  65:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Address phase : the mode used and if present the size, the address
  66:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****          value and the DTR mode.
  67:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Alternate-bytes phase : the mode used and if present the size, the
  68:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****          alternate bytes values and the DTR mode.
  69:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Dummy-cycles phase : the number of dummy cycles (mode used is same as data phase).
  70:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Data phase : the mode used and if present the number of bytes and the DTR mode.
  71:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Data strobe (DQS) mode : the activation (or not) of this mode
  72:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Sending Instruction Only Once (SIOO) mode : the activation (or not) of this mode.
  73:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Flash identifier : in dual-quad mode, indicates which flash is concerned
  74:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Operation type : always common configuration
  75:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     [..]
  76:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      In Hyperbus mode, configure the command sequence using the HAL_OSPI_HyperbusCmd()
  77:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      function :
  78:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Address space : indicate if the access will be done in register or memory
  79:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Address size
  80:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Number of data
  81:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) Data strobe (DQS) mode : the activation (or not) of this mode
  82:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     [..]
  83:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      If no data is required for the command (only for regular mode, not for
  84:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      Hyperbus mode), it is sent directly to the memory :
  85:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) In polling mode, the output of the function is done when the transfer is complete.
  86:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) In interrupt mode, HAL_OSPI_CmdCpltCallback() will be called when the transfer is complete
  87:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     [..]
  88:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      For the indirect write mode, use HAL_OSPI_Transmit(), HAL_OSPI_Transmit_DMA() or
ARM GAS  /var/folders/cy/8kgpsxf90rz6cg1g85ws44fm0000gn/T//ccAhGhcL.s 			page 3


  89:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      HAL_OSPI_Transmit_IT() after the command configuration :
  90:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) In polling mode, the output of the function is done when the transfer is complete.
  91:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) In interrupt mode, HAL_OSPI_FifoThresholdCallback() will be called when the fifo threshold
  92:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****          is reached and HAL_OSPI_TxCpltCallback() will be called when the transfer is complete.
  93:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) In DMA mode, HAL_OSPI_TxHalfCpltCallback() will be called at the half transfer and
  94:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****          HAL_OSPI_TxCpltCallback() will be called when the transfer is complete.
  95:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     [..]
  96:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      For the indirect read mode, use HAL_OSPI_Receive(), HAL_OSPI_Receive_DMA() or
  97:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      HAL_OSPI_Receive_IT() after the command configuration :
  98:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) In polling mode, the output of the function is done when the transfer is complete.
  99:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) In interrupt mode, HAL_OSPI_FifoThresholdCallback() will be called when the fifo threshold
 100:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****          is reached and HAL_OSPI_RxCpltCallback() will be called when the transfer is complete.
 101:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) In DMA mode, HAL_OSPI_RxHalfCpltCallback() will be called at the half transfer and
 102:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****          HAL_OSPI_RxCpltCallback() will be called when the transfer is complete.
