 109:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      Configure the auto-polling functional mode using the HAL_OSPI_AutoPolling()
 110:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      or HAL_OSPI_AutoPolling_IT() functions :
 111:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) The size of the status bytes, the match value, the mask used, the match mode (OR/AND),
 112:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****          the polling interval and the automatic stop activation.
 113:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     [..]
 114:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      After the configuration :
 115:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) In polling mode, the output of the function is done when the status match is reached. The
 116:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****          automatic stop is activated to avoid an infinite loop.
 117:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) In interrupt mode, HAL_OSPI_StatusMatchCallback() will be called each time the status matc
